4
The mists of Halong Bay ...
Jan 2020
So much has already been written about "Halong Bay" ... I'll be quite brief. As a Unesco 1994 appointed "World Heritage Site", "Halong Bay" is absolutely unmissable by all those travelling in Northeast Vietnam and Hanoi area. Its magic mists will definitely bewitch you! Emerald waters and infinite towering limestone isles, islets and caves topped by lush rainforests. All aging 20 million years! Board a boat (and there are very many different options from simple junks to luxury cruises) and discover the secrets of "Halong Bay". In Vietnamese, "Halong" means "Descending Dragon" - just like a mythological dragon descending from heaven and breaking through the limestones rocks and deep waters of the bay! A miracle of endless beauty! Enjoy!
Written November 16, 2020
